12/09/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The OSCE Chairman-in-Office, Belgian Foreign Minister Karel De Gucht, denounced on Monday (11 September) the violence Sunday that marred the extraordinary vote for members of the local assembly in Serbia's mainly Muslim-populated municipality of Novi Pazar.
A candidate from the winning List for Sandzak coalition, Ruzdija Durovic, was killed and another man was badly injured in a shooting in front of a polling station.
Novi Pazar police confirm that two people have been detained and a third is being sought in connection with the shootings.
(Politika - 12/09/06;
OSCE website, Tanjug - 11/09/06)
